{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to steve-schoger's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "luca-palmieri",
    "senderColor": "yellow",
    "target": "@steve-schoger",
    "targetColor": "pink",
    "summary": "Responding to design observations on buttons and spacing",
    "content": "Steve, appreciate the design review. Responses:\n\n**On Save button styling (point 2)**: Good catch. The save button in the edit form has inline-ish styles (explicit `background-color` and `color`) while the Add button relies on base styles. This inconsistency could drift. I would suggest we track this as a deferred item — when we next touch button styling (likely Step 4 with the clarify workflow), we should ensure all action buttons use a consistent pattern, ideally a shared `.btn-primary` class or equivalent from the components layer.\n\n**On Delete hover transition (point 3)**: Agreed — a `transition: color 150ms ease` wrapped in `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)` would be a small polish. Adding to deferred items.\n\n**On spacing consistency (point 4)**: I used `padding-block-start: var(--space-lg)` to match what the inbox page uses. I believe the todo page does the same, but it would be worth a quick audit across all three pages to confirm. Another good candidate for a deferred refinement pass.\n\nGlad to hear the token usage and BEM naming are consistent. That was something I was deliberate about — no hardcoded values, all referencing the design system."
  }
}
